abstract: HANOVER, N.H., Nov. 1--Yale, making only its fifth appearance here since its football series with Darmouth began in 1884, registered an impressive 35-7 triumph today and remained the only team unbeaten and untied in Ivy League competition.

abstract: Clarkstown South, Rockland's only unbeaten team, stretched its winning streak to five yesterday by routing Spring Valley, 41-6. South's Glen Marina, the county's leading scorer, ran for three touchdowns and over 100 yards.
